oai_dc:dc.dc:title: State Capitol of Tennessee, new interior of Governor’s Office, 1938 August
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A view of the new interior of the Tennessee Governor’s Office at the State Capitol Building in Nashville, Tennessee, August, 1938. Governor Gordon Browning served in office from 1937 to 1939, and again from 1949 to 1953. Forms part of Record Group 412, Photographs Collection. 1 photograph negative : b & w ; 4 x 5 in.
